<h2>Purpose</h2>
<p>
  Capability grounding for <a href="/backlog/488-on-device-ui-screenshot-vision-model-as-a-plateau-capability/">backlog #488</a>:
  whether Plateau should back its vision-dependent features with an <strong>owned on-device model</strong>
  (fixed cost, so it can sit inside flat-rate pricing under the <em>linear-cost-with-revenue</em> rule)
  rather than only a metered hosted SDK. The sub-question with no prior analysis — <em>what can an
  on-device UI-vision model actually do, and is it feasible now?</em> — is answered here. Session report:
  <code>reports/2026-06-13-on-device-ui-vision-capability.md</code>.
</p>

<h2>The decisive finding — the gate verdict is coarse classification, not understanding</h2>
<p>
  The capture-QC verdict (app / obstructed / marketing / error / blank / non-app — six classes) is a
  <strong>screen-classification</strong> task, not generative understanding. That makes it small.
</p>
